:: a billion dollars
The devil hands you the crusty black suitcase lined with hundred dollar bills,
totalling one billion dollars.

~end~

:: you raise the billion
After checking your bank account one rainy morning, you phone up the devil.
<<set $billion = true>>

"Okay," you say. "I've acquired the billion dollars -- now, at last... I
believe you owe me whatever I want."

The devil acknowledges you slyly and moments later appears at your door.

You, eyebrow perked with anticipation, hastily hand over your crusty black
suitcase lined with hundreds, totalling one billion dollars, to the devil.

He accepts it by the handle and, without a word, touches your shoulder. The
world wobbles around you and then suddenly seems [[very distantly familiar|time
travel]].

:: choice
"On a whim, as I'm bored with the lack of chance as to the fate of my riches,"
says the devil, "I'd like to offer you one of the following:
(a) [[a billion dollars|no choice]], or
(b) [[anything you want, provided you give me a billion dollars|no choice]]."

