:: StoryTitle
The Devil of the Excluded Middle

:: anything you want, provided you give me a billion dollars
You scoff at the Devil's presumptousness -- of course this what he'd select,
and it's hardly any favor. But as years wear on, the offer gnaws at you, and
you imagine the possibilities of being granted that wish.

With new resolve, you do everything you can - beg, steal, lie, cheat, lead a
life of crime and then con your way into the control of major corporations,
whittling your entire life away with the devil's voice at your back, ultimately
doing his service. You hurt many people. You grow old.

But, after all that time, [[you raise the billion]].


